1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:09,000
Taking walks and playing games when there's sunny weather

2
00:00:09,000 --> 00:00:15,000
If there's rain, they're singing songs or reading books together

3
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:21,000
Every day just has a way of feeling extra lucky

4
00:00:21,000 --> 00:00:26,000
When you spend it with a friend, just like Bjorn and Bucky

5
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:29,000
Just like Bjorn and Bucky!

6
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:33,000
Star Story!

7
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:40,000
Big Dipper, Ursa Major Great Bear

8
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:42,000
What a kick!

9
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:45,000
Ursa Minor Little Bear

10
00:00:45,000 --> 00:00:47,000
Cassiopeia

11
00:00:49,000 --> 00:00:51,000
Bucky!

12
00:00:51,000 --> 00:00:54,000
Enough reading, let's go and play!

13
00:00:54,000 --> 00:00:56,000
I can't now, sorry Bucky

14
00:00:56,000 --> 00:00:59,000
I'm supposed to study

15
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:04,000
Ursa Major Great Bear, Ursa Minor Little Bear

16
00:01:04,000 --> 00:01:06,000
The Atlas of the Stars, huh?

17
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:09,000
Why do you want to learn about the stars?

18
00:01:09,000 --> 00:01:15,000
Polar bears all have to really know every single constellation in the sky

19
00:01:15,000 --> 00:01:19,000
Well, a book won't do it

20
00:01:19,000 --> 00:01:22,000
You need to be looking at the stars in real life, Bjorn

21
00:01:22,000 --> 00:01:24,000
And you can't see them in the day

22
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:27,000
Well at night, I can't read the Atlas

23
00:01:27,000 --> 00:01:30,000
And I get really snoozy woozy

24
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:33,000
You need to visit a planetarium!

25
00:01:33,000 --> 00:01:34,000
Do what?

26
00:01:34,000 --> 00:01:35,000
What?

27
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:40,000
You know, the building where you can look at the stars whenever you want to, even in the daytime

28
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:42,000
And do planetariums just grow in the forest?

29
00:01:42,000 --> 00:01:44,000
Um, not really

30
00:01:44,000 --> 00:01:49,000
Well I guess, I'll have to learn the stars by using the book

31
00:01:49,000 --> 00:01:51,000
Hmm

32
00:01:51,000 --> 00:01:53,000
You know what?

33
00:01:53,000 --> 00:01:56,000
It so happens that the world's greatest planetarium is...

34
00:01:56,000 --> 00:01:58,000
Right in my own cabin!

35
00:01:58,000 --> 00:02:00,000
Or I will be really soon!

36
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:03,000
I need this for something

37
00:02:03,000 --> 00:02:05,000
Give me half an hour, then come see

38
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:07,000
I'm a genius!

39
00:02:07,000 --> 00:02:09,000
Time to be awesome!

40
00:02:09,000 --> 00:02:16,000
Big Dipper goes here!

41
00:02:16,000 --> 00:02:19,000
Fancy glass!

42
00:02:19,000 --> 00:02:21,000
Teacup!

43
00:02:21,000 --> 00:02:22,000
This is fun!

44
00:02:22,000 --> 00:02:26,000
I'm making constellations, baby!

45
00:02:26,000 --> 00:02:27,000
Tree stand!

46
00:02:27,000 --> 00:02:28,000
Bowl!

47
00:02:28,000 --> 00:02:30,000
Hammer thing!

48
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:33,000
Bucky, you are the coolest friend ever!

49
00:02:33,000 --> 00:02:34,000
Yeah!

50
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:36,000
Hey there, Bjorn!

51
00:02:36,000 --> 00:02:38,000
You got here right on time!

52
00:02:39,000 --> 00:02:40,000
Come in!

53
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:42,000
Welcome to the Bucky Way galaxy!

54
00:02:42,000 --> 00:02:43,000
Ooh!

55
00:02:43,000 --> 00:02:45,000
It's a planetary...

56
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:47,000
Nice try, dude!

57
00:02:47,000 --> 00:02:49,000
But there's no polar bear constellation!

58
00:02:49,000 --> 00:02:51,000
Seems like you'd know that!

59
00:02:51,000 --> 00:02:53,000
This is a planetarium, is it?

60
00:02:53,000 --> 00:02:55,000
What's going on with the ropes everywhere?

61
00:02:55,000 --> 00:02:56,000
Just ignore that!

62
00:02:56,000 --> 00:02:58,000
All the other stuff's what you're here to see!

63
00:02:58,000 --> 00:03:00,000
Bjorn Bear, come on down!

64
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:03,000
Prepare to have your mind blown!

65
00:03:03,000 --> 00:03:06,000
Just over here is Ursa Major, the great bear pod!

66
00:03:06,000 --> 00:03:08,000
It's totally just like the real thing!

67
00:03:08,000 --> 00:03:10,000
Almost exactly kinda!

68
00:03:10,000 --> 00:03:11,000
Up here's the great cup!

69
00:03:11,000 --> 00:03:13,000
And down here's the great broken cup!

70
00:03:13,000 --> 00:03:16,000
Alright, maybe that's not a real constellation!

71
00:03:16,000 --> 00:03:18,000
Uh, how come you hung a hammer?

72
00:03:18,000 --> 00:03:21,000
Well, you see, so it occurred to me!

73
00:03:21,000 --> 00:03:25,000
There's so many stars, there's gotta be one hammer constellation up there!

74
00:03:25,000 --> 00:03:27,000
I give you nail hit us major!

75
00:03:27,000 --> 00:03:29,000
So I made a few up!

76
00:03:29,000 --> 00:03:30,000
It's cool though, right?

77
00:03:30,000 --> 00:03:31,000
It fills an open space!

78
00:03:31,000 --> 00:03:32,000
Huh?

79
00:03:32,000 --> 00:03:33,000
Bjorn, wait!

80
00:03:33,000 --> 00:03:34,000
Where are you going?

81
00:03:34,000 --> 00:03:35,000
What's wrong?

82
00:03:36,000 --> 00:03:37,000
Bjorn?

83
00:03:37,000 --> 00:03:39,000
Are you upset or something?

84
00:03:41,000 --> 00:03:42,000
Hey listen!

85
00:03:42,000 --> 00:03:45,000
I can take the hammer down if that's what's wrong!

86
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:49,000
Although it is pretty bangin', if I do say so myself!

87
00:03:49,000 --> 00:03:52,000
There's not a hammer constellation in the sky!

88
00:03:52,000 --> 00:03:54,000
Uh, I can fix everything, you know!

89
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:57,000
Make sure it's super accurate so you can study the stars for real!

90
00:03:57,000 --> 00:04:00,000
I'm better off studying out here!

91
00:04:00,000 --> 00:04:03,000
Thanks a lot, but your planetarium just isn't my...

92
00:04:03,000 --> 00:04:05,000
Please tell me you see those lights!

93
00:04:05,000 --> 00:04:07,000
Look at that!

94
00:04:07,000 --> 00:04:08,000
Fireflies!

95
00:04:08,000 --> 00:04:09,000
Isn't it pretty?

96
00:04:09,000 --> 00:04:12,000
I wish my behind glowed like that!

97
00:04:12,000 --> 00:04:13,000
Wow!

98
00:04:13,000 --> 00:04:15,000
That looks like the big dipper!

99
00:04:15,000 --> 00:04:19,000
I think it actually looks closer to the great bear!

100
00:04:19,000 --> 00:04:21,000
Mmm, Cassiopeia!

101
00:04:21,000 --> 00:04:22,000
Hey!

102
00:04:22,000 --> 00:04:25,000
Just like you said, Bjorn!

103
00:04:25,000 --> 00:04:28,000
That you wanted to learn about constellations out here?

104
00:04:28,000 --> 00:04:30,000
Well, that's just what's happening!

105
00:04:30,000 --> 00:04:33,000
Nature's showing us all the constellations!

106
00:04:34,000 --> 00:04:35,000
See?

107
00:04:35,000 --> 00:04:38,000
That looks like the constellation Leo Minor, Bucky!

108
00:04:38,000 --> 00:04:39,000
Nice kitty!

109
00:04:40,000 --> 00:04:42,000
And that's Pisces!

110
00:04:42,000 --> 00:04:44,000
Something's fishy about that one!

111
00:04:45,000 --> 00:04:47,000
There's Perseus!

112
00:04:47,000 --> 00:04:48,000
Hey, Skyman!

113
00:04:48,000 --> 00:04:50,000
And Orion!

114
00:04:50,000 --> 00:04:51,000
Hey, other Skyman!

115
00:04:51,000 --> 00:04:52,000
That looks like Scorpio!

116
00:04:52,000 --> 00:04:54,000
That is a big scorpion!

117
00:04:54,000 --> 00:04:55,000
And there's Aquarius!

118
00:04:55,000 --> 00:04:57,000
You're spilling your water, dude!

119
00:04:57,000 --> 00:04:58,000
Ooh!

120
00:04:58,000 --> 00:04:59,000
There's the Milky Way!

121
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:04,000
Owl said it isn't the Milky Way!

122
00:05:04,000 --> 00:05:07,000
Instead, it's a meteor shower that's learned to dance and do tricks!

123
00:05:09,000 --> 00:05:12,000
That shows how well you understand owl language!

124
00:05:12,000 --> 00:05:17,000
What it really said was, we should all be in bed now, because it's quite late!

125
00:05:17,000 --> 00:05:20,000
Well then, I'll say goodnight Bjorn, my friend!

126
00:05:20,000 --> 00:05:23,000
Try not to let that hammer fall on your head!

127
00:05:23,000 --> 00:05:24,000
Hehehe!

128
00:05:24,000 --> 00:05:25,000
Hehehe!

129
00:05:25,000 --> 00:05:26,000
Hehehe!

130
00:05:28,000 --> 00:05:30,000
The End

131
00:05:30,000 --> 00:05:34,000
Cars

